---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Scrabble Words With Prefix RE- — REWORK, REVAMP, RETURN" description="Top RE- prefix Scrabble words: REWORK (13pts), REVAMP (13pts), RETURN (6pts). Master the repeat prefix for front hooks and board extension plays." keywords="scrabble re prefix words, rework scrabble, revamp scrabble, return scrabble, re prefix strategy, repeat prefix scrabble">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words With Prefix RE- — REWORK, REVAMP, RETURN","description":"Master RE- prefix words in Scrabble: REWORK (13pts), REVAMP (13pts), RETURN (6pts) with repeat prefix strategy.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-with-prefix-re"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the best RE- prefix words in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"REWORK (13pts) and REVAMP (13pts) tie for the top spot — both use high-value consonants (W=4, K=5 and V=4, M=3, P=3). RETURN scores only 6 points but is extremely common and easy to play in tight board positions."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many valid RE- words exist in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Over 1,000 valid RE- words exist in the SOWPODS dictionary. RE- is the most productive prefix in English, attaching to almost any verb to mean 'again' — REDO, REMAKE, REWORK, REVAMP, RETURN, REWIND, REFUND, REFORM."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"When should you use RE- as a front hook?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Use RE- when WORK, VAMP, TURN, WIND, FUND, or FORM are already on the board. Adding RE costs only 2 tiles (R=1, E=1) but scores the entire new word. This is especially powerful when the base word sits near premium squares."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Strategy</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words With Prefix RE- — Repeat Prefix Guide</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">RE- is the most prolific prefix in Scrabble — over 1,000 valid words start with it. At just 2 points cost (R=1, E=1), it front-hooks onto existing board words for massive value. REWORK and REVAMP both score 13 points thanks to premium consonants, while RETURN offers a reliable 6-point play from the most common tiles in the bag.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Top Score (REWORK/REVAMP)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Prefix Tiles (RE)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1000+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid RE- Words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Prefix Cost (R+E)</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top RE- Prefix Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 REWORK</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 points · 6 letters · R(1)+E(1)+W(4)+O(1)+R(1)+K(5) · W+K = 9pts</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 REVAMP</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 points · 6 letters · R(1)+E(1)+V(4)+A(1)+M(3)+P(3) · V+M+P = 10pts</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ RETURN</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">6 points · 6 letters · R(1)+E(1)+T(1)+U(1)+R(1)+N(1) · All common tiles</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ RESTOCK</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 points · 7 letters · R(1)+E(1)+S(1)+T(1)+O(1)+C(3)+K(5) · Bingo eligible</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">RE- Prefix Strategy</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">The cheapest front hook:</span> R and E are both 1-point tiles with 6+ copies in the bag. You'll almost always have RE available. Scan the board constantly for WORK, VAMP, TURN, WIND, FUND — each becomes a RE- word.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">RE- for bingo extensions:</span> RESTOCK (7), RESTYLE (7), RESHAPE (7), REQUIRE (7). Many RE- words hit exactly 7 letters for the bingo bonus. If your rack has R+E plus a 5-letter word, check if RE+root works.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Stack with suffixes:</span> RE- words often take -ED, -ING, -S endings. REWORK→REWORKED (8 letters, bingo), REVAMP→REVAMPED (8), RETURN→RETURNED (8). The prefix + suffix combo creates long words from short roots.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">REWORK</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">REVAMP</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">RETURN</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">RESTOCK</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">RE- is the <span class="text-white font-medium">most productive prefix in English</span> with 1,000+ valid Scrabble words. At only 2 points invested, every front hook earns back 5-15x the cost. Keep R+E in mind every turn — the board almost always has a hookable word.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-starting-with-re/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Starting With RE-</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-with-prefix-un/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words With Prefix UN-</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/complete-guide-to-hooks/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Complete Guide to Hooks</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find all RE- prefix words from your tiles — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
